rComments: Good prof, understanding of pressures (Especially in a first year grad school course). It's an intro course, so most of the material is kind of dull, but Alex did a great job of making it interesting and engaging

One of the best professors out there! He will talk and joke and while doing it, he will actually make you learn and think. He is easy going and accommodating and actually teaches things that are required. He will joke about this cat "Chapa" his love for drinks, alcohol and beers. and the famous SUZUKI (i do not know the guy). He loves to laugh!

Alexander is hilarious and engaging. I really enjoyed his class. He was always interested in class participation , but not really encouraging of critical thinking - more just looking for students to get the course content and not think too far out of the box.
